ng:</strong> $$\quad f'(x) = \Big(\frac{\cos x}{\sin x}\Big)' = \frac{-\sin x \sin x - \cos x \cos x}{\sin^2x} = \frac{-(\sin^2x + \cos^2x)}{\sin^2x} = -\frac{1}{\sin^2x}$$</p><p>$$\qquad\qquad\quad$$ bzw. $$\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad\quad \dots \;\;\;= -\Big(\frac{\sin x}{\sin x}\Big)^2 - \Big(\frac{\cos x}{\sin x}\Big)^2 = -1-\cot^2x$$</p></modalFeedback></assessmentItem>
